responseMessageContents.text:
This is a **Firestore security rules** issue, not a code bug. The `permission-denied` error means your Firebase Firestore rules are blocking the write operation to the `equipmentRequests` collection.

You need to update your Firestore security rules in the **Firebase Console**:

1. Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com)
2. Select your project
3. Navigate to **Firestore Database → Rules**
4. Update the rules to allow authenticated users to create requests. For example:

```
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {

    // Equipment - anyone can read, authenticated users can write their own
    match /equipment/{equipmentId} {
      allow read: if true;
      allow create: if request.auth != null;
      allow update, delete: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == resource.data.ownerUid;
    }

    // Equipment Requests
    match /equipmentRequests/{requestId} {
      allow read: if request.auth != null && 
        (request.auth.uid == resource.data.customerUid || request.auth.uid == resource.data.providerUid);
      allow create: if request.auth != null;
      allow update: if request.auth != null && 
        (request.auth.uid == resource.data.customerUid || request.auth.uid == resource.data.providerUid);

      // Messages subcollection
      match /messages/{messageId} {
        allow read, write: if request.auth != null;
      }
    }

    // Users
    match /users/{userId} {
      allow read: if true;
      allow write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == userId;
    }

    // Ratings
    match /ratings/{ratingId} {
      allow read: if true;
      allow create: if request.auth != null;
    }

    // Invoices
    match /invoices/{invoiceId} {
      allow read: if request.auth != null;
      allow create: if request.auth != null;
    }
  }
}
```

5. Click **Publish**

This grants authenticated users permission to create requests while keeping reads/updates scoped to participants. The error will resolve once the rules are published.
